payload.creator: AlysCole
payload.comment:
Fix the behavior of the backspace key, wherein when the caret is at
the beginning of an existing line, nothing is done. When pressed with
the caret at the beginning of a line, the backspace key should now
combine the current line and previous line at the previous row.

Close issue #49.

payload.creator: AlysCole
payload.comment:
This commit will separate the function 'updateCaret' into two:
'updateCaretAtInput' (handles the movement of the caret when data is
entered/deleted) and 'updateCaretAtSpecialKey' (handles the movement
of the caret when a key is pressed).

The added function 'updateCaretAtSpecialKey' will handle the movement
of the caret by the arrow keys (left, up, right, and down).

Close issue #52.

commits.author: AlysCole
commits.message:
Combine separated updateCaret functions into single 'updateCaret'

Modify code to combine previously separated updateCaret
functions (updateCaretAtInput and updateCaretAtSpecialKey) into one
function, updateCaret. The check for 'listOfSpecialKeys' should keep
special keys from moving the caret to (offset + 1), as is the default
switch case for the function updateCaret.

Also, introduce a minor fix so that the down arrow key checks the next
line's length for its offset, rather than the previous line.
